19
00:01:20,850 --> 00:01:24,040
In this unit we studied four main topics

20
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:30,049
1. How an application uses the Internet. Phil explained the common way in which a variety

21
00:01:30,049 --> 00:01:35,439
of different applications use the Internet, using Skype, BitTorrent and the Web as specific

22
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:40,310
examples. You learned that most applications want to communicate over a reliable, bi-directional

23
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:44,619
byte-stream between two or more end points.

24
00:01:44,619 --> 00:01:51,619
2. The structure of the Internet. You learnd what the 4-layer model is, and the responsibility

25
00:01:52,110 --> 00:01:57,149
of each layer. You also learned why we use the Internet Protocol or “IP” every time

26
00:01:57,149 --> 00:02:02,450
we send packets across the Internet, and why we call IP the “thin waist” of the Internet.

27
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:09,450
3. The Internet protocol (IP). Because IP is so important, we spent several videos describing

28
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:17,120
what IP does for us, and how it works. So far we’ve focussed on IP version 4, because

29
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:21,660
it’s the most widely used version of IP today. You’ll learn about IP addresses,

30
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:26,640
how routers look up IP addresses and so on. Later in the course you’ll learn about the

31
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:31,380
